cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with the generation of adversarial traffic signs that can fool image classification systems, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses attacks on image classification systems, which can be considered a security issue. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper involves the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques to generate and test adversarial images. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with the use of AI techniques to generate and test adversarial images. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves testing the efficiency of the attacks on a real production-grade traffic sign recognition system, which can be considered a control system.
